title.rendered: South Africa vs West Indies, 3rd T20I: Fantasy Team, Probable Playing XIs, Pitch Report & Fantasy Tips

content.rendered:
South Africa vs West Indies, 3rd T20I Fantasy Team

We have opted for a fantasy cricket team on basis of probable XIs, recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable Playing XIs for South Africa & West Indies

South Africa: Quinton de Kock (wk), Reeza Hendricks, Rilee Rossouw, Aiden Markram (c), David Miller, Heinrich Klaasen, Marco Jansen, Wayne Parnell, Sisanda Magala, Kagiso Rabada, Tabraiz Shamsi

West Indies: Kyle Mayers, Brandon King, Johnson Charles, Nicholas Pooran (wk), Rovman Powell (c), Romario Shepherd, Odean Smith, Jason Holder, Raymon Reifer, Akeal Hosein, Sheldon Cottrell

The Wanderers Stadium, Johannesburg Pitch Report

Venue: The Wanderers Stadium, Johannesburg

(Based on last three matches)

1st innings average score: 175

2nd innings average score: 160

Wickets per innings: 7

Type: Good for batting

Wins

Batting 1st: 33%

Batting 2nd: 67%

Also Read:

Afghanistan vs Pakistan, 3rd T20I 2023: Fantasy Tips

Gujarat vs Chennai, Indian T20 League 2023: Fantasy Tips

Fantasy Tips of The Day

Quinton de Kock has a special liking for the West Indies bowlers. Against them, he has scored 402 runs in eight innings, including a century, three half-centuries, and two thirties. He has also given 76 points for catches.

Johnson Charles has been one of the most popular picks in T20s in 2023. He has scored 454 runs at an average of 57, with the help of two centuries.

So has Rovman Powell, who has scored 260 runs at an average of 32.5 in T20s played this year. He has also grabbed four catches and picked wickets in both the games he bowled.

Odean Smith picked a wicket or more in 10 of the last 11 T20Is, overall taking 17 wickets at a strike rate of 12.

Romario Shepherd scored 99 runs at 49.5, picked three wickets, and grabbed two catches in the last five T20s.

Reeza Hendricks has generated a 30- or 50-run bonus in four of the last six T20 innings, aggregating 270 runs at 45. He has also pouched four catches.

Aiden Markram has collected 216 runs at 54, while also giving points for six catches in as many matches.

Marco Jansen hasn’t gone wicketless in the last six competitive T20s, scalping eight wickets at 13.8.

Kagiso Rabada has gone wicketless in eight of his last 15 T20Is, scalping only one wicket each in the remaining games.

Jason Holder has ordinary numbers in the last five competitive T20 matches: 56 runs and one wicket.
